properties.Name: AircraftFamilyModelConfiguration
properties.Description: An Aircraft Family Model Configuration of specific seat, amenity etc. configurations.

Columns.Name: AircraftFamilyModelId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Aircraft Family Model.

Columns.Name: ConfigurationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a configuration.

Columns.Name: EmptyWeight
Columns.Description: The empty weight of the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: TakeoffWeight
Columns.Description: The takeoff weight of the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: GrossWeight
Columns.Description: The gross weight of the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: CruiseSpeed
Columns.Description: The cruising speed of the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: CruiseAltitude
Columns.Description: The recommended cruising altitude of the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: MaximumOperationalAltitude
Columns.Description: The maximum operating altitude of the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: TakeoffRoll
Columns.Description: The length of runway required for the aircraft family model configuration to takeoff.

Columns.Name: Range
Columns.Description: Distance an aircraft family model configuration can fly or is permitted to fly with a specified load and (usually) after making allowances for specified maneuvers such as diversions, stand-off, go-around.

Columns.Name: RangeWithMaximumPayload
Columns.Description: The range of the aircraft family model configuration with a maximum payload.

Columns.Name: MaximumNumberOfPassengers
Columns.Description: The maximum number of passengers in the associated aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: MaximumNumberOfFirstClassPassengers
Columns.Description: The maximum number of first class passengers that may be carried by the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: MaximumNumberOfBusinessClassPassengers
Columns.Description: The maximum number of business class passengers that may be carried by the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: MaximumNumberOfEconomyPassengers
Columns.Description: The maximum number of economy class passengers that may be carried by the aircraft family model configuration.

Columns.Name: AircraftFamilyModelConfigurationNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the aircraft family model configuration.
